BILL NO. 36-0090
Thirty-Sixth Legislature of the Virgin Islands
May 19, 2025
An act amending title 1 Virgin Islands Code, chapter 11 by adding section 200m to declare the
week beginning the Monday before the first Friday in June as the Virgin Islands Gun Violence
Awareness Week
PROPOSED BY: Senator Angel L. Bolques, Jr.
1 WHEREAS, gun violence continues to be a significant public health and safety issue in
2 the Virgin Islands, with profound impacts on individuals, families, and communities at large;
3 and
4 WHEREAS, on March 13, 2019, the 33rd Legislature passed Bill No. 33-0126
5 establishing the Office of Gun Violence Prevention under the Office of the Governor.
6 WHEREAS, according to recent data, the Virgin Islands has experienced a disturbingly
7 high rate of gun violence, with 43 homicides reported in 2024 alone, the majority of which
8 involved firearms; and
9 WHEREAS, a study revealed that the average homicide rate in the Virgin Islands was
10 approximately 37.4 per 100,000 residents per year between 1999 and 2014, significantly higher
11 than many other Caribbean islands and U.S. cities; and

2
1 WHEREAS, in 2020, the Virgin Islands had a homicide rate nine times higher than the
2 mainland United States emphasizing the severity of gun violence in the territory; and
3 WHEREAS, the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) reported that the
4 Virgin Islands has one of the highest per capita rates of gun deaths in the United States,
5 highlighting the urgent need for community-based interventions and awareness campaigns; and
6 WHEREAS, gun violence has long-lasting physical, emotional, and psychological
7 effects on survivors and their families, contributing to trauma and a cycle of violence; and
8 WHEREAS, declaring a specific week dedicated to gun violence awareness provides an
9 opportunity for residents, community organizations, and the local government to come together
10 to address this critical issue and work towards solutions; and
11 WHEREAS, Virgin Islands Gun Violence Awareness Week will encourage educational
12 activities, community discussions, and initiatives aimed at preventing gun violence and
13 supporting affected individuals and communities; and
14 WHEREAS, promoting gun violence awareness aligns with the broader goals of
15 enhancing public safety, fostering a sense of community, and improving the overall well-being
16 of Virgin Islands residents; Now Therefore,
17 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the Virgin Islands:
18 SECTION 1. Title 1, Virgin Islands Code, chapter 11 is amended by adding the following
19 section 200m:
20 § 200m. Virgin Islands Gun Violence Awareness Week
21 (a) The week beginning the Monday before the first Friday in June is designated as
22 “Virgin Islands Gun Violence Awareness Week” in alignment with annual National Gun
23 Violence Awareness Day. Virgin Islands Gun Violence Awareness Week is an observance and
24 not a holiday.
25 (b) Virgin Islands Gun Violence Awareness Week shall be observed as a week to raise

3
1 awareness about gun violence, to honor and to remember victims and survivors of gun
2 violence, and to promote efforts to reduce gun violence in our communities.
3 BILL SUMMARY
4 This bill amends title 1, Virgin Islands Code, chapter 11 by establishing the Virgin
5 Islands National Gun Violence Awareness Week beginning on the Monday preceding the first
6 Friday in June in alignment with the National Gun Violence Awareness Day.
